
** Search Word at Current Point

  - *C-s M-e* Edit the current search string

  - *C-s M-y* Yank the current kill. Unfortunately M-y again is not
    possible.

  - *M-b C-s C-w* This moves first the cursor to the beginning of the
    word and then starts the search mode and selects the current
    word. 

** Isearch

  - C-u C-s starts with isearch regexp

  - C-w   yank-word-or-char
  - C-y   yank rest of line
  - C-M-w modify yanked search string - backward
  - C-M-y modify yanked search string - forward
  - C-j   newline
  - M-e   edit search
  - M-c   toggle case sensitive search. Also a upper-case letter turns 
          on case sensitive search.
  - M-r   toggle regexp search
  - M-p   search ring
  - M-n   search ring
  - M-s w word search

  - *C-h C-h* help for isearch

** Occur

  - *isearch-occur*
  - *multi-occur* > 21.3.50. See also igrep and ibuffer.

  - *C-o* Do not leave the occur buffer.
